modules.description: Provides functions to resolve domain names and establish TCP connections using the Happy Eyeballs algorithm. Operates on domain names, IP addresses, and TCP flow structures. Used to efficiently connect to servers by attempting multiple IP addresses in parallel, improving reliability and reducing latency.

Provides functions for making HTTP requests, resolving domain names using happy-eyeballs, and handling TLS connections with ocaml-tls. Works with URLs, sockets, and TLS configurations. Used to establish reliable HTTP connections in constrained environments like unikernels.

Establishes an HTTP connection using a provided Mimic context, returning a client handle wrapped in a Lwt promise. Operates on Mimic's context type and abstract client type to manage network interactions. Used to initiate HTTP requests in a non-blocking, asynchronous manner within MirageOS environments.
